  "patient_summary": "Olivia is a 73-year-old female with a medical history including Hyperlipidemia associated with type 2 diabetes mellitus, mixed dyslipidemia, essential hypertension, and postoperative anemia. She is a former smoker, having quit in 1991, and does not currently consume alcohol. Recent lab results indicate elevated Ferritin (266.8 ng/mL) and low Iron (41 ug/dL) and Iron Saturation (15%). Her blood pressure was recorded at 128/78 on 01/11/2025. She has had prior infections with MRSA (resolved 03/29/2023) and COVID-19 (recovered 01/24/2021). Her functional status indicates difficulty walking or climbing stairs but adequate vision and no hearing, dressing, bathing, or cognitive difficulties. Key goals include blood pressure management, diabetes medication adherence, regular blood sugar checks (with target ranges), and an upcoming eye doctor appointment which is currently not on track. She wishes to discontinue insulin."
